---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy | Mod Labs"
  description="How Mod Labs collects, uses, and retains information when you request a quote, book a time, or send a console for service."
>
  <section class="hero-gradient border-bottom border-brand py-5">
    <div class="container" data-aos="fade-up">
      <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold section-title mb-2">Privacy</h1>
      <p class="text-muted-brand lead mb-0">Plain-language summary — adjust with your legal counsel if needed.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-5">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-lg-8 text-muted-brand" data-aos="fade-up">
          <h2 class="h5 text-light fw-bold mt-4">What we collect</h2>
          <p>
            When you use the quote form, we collect the fields you submit (such as name, email, phone if provided, device details, and your message). Booking widgets may collect scheduling data according to the provider you connect (for example Cal.com or Calendly).
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 text-light fw-bold mt-4">Why we use it</h2>
          <p>
            Information is used to respond to requests, schedule work, and coordinate shipping or drop-off. We do not sell personal data.
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 text-light fw-bold mt-4">How long we keep it</h2>
          <p>
            Quote and booking records are kept only as long as needed for the job and reasonable business records unless a longer period is required by law.
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 text-light fw-bold mt-4">Devices &amp; data on hardware</h2>
          <p class="mb-0">
            Consoles may contain your accounts and saves. You are responsible for backing up data where possible. Typical mod installs do not require wiping storage.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
